Court corrects the record that defendant entered pleas to 2 cts. Substantial battery and the parties will proceed on that correction.  Defense counsel is in agreement with this.  
Count 1 - Substantial battery - Sentence is withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.  Conditions of probation are:
1) Spend twelve (12) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, to commence on 05-02-15 at 8:00 a.m.  Transfer to Brown County Jail is authorized or in the alternative travel outside the county for purposes of employment.  
2) Attend anger management counseling and follow through;
3) Maintain absolute sobriety;
4) AODA assessment and follow through counseling;
5) Pay $29,288.85 restitution to John Becker;
6) Maintain full-time employment;
7) Pay costs of action;
8) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
9) Provide DNA sample and pay;
10) No contact with the victims without agent's approval;
Count 2 - Substantial battery - Sentence is withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years, concurrent with Count 1.  Conditions of probation are:
1) Spend two (2) months in jail, under the Huber Law, consecutive to count 1.  
2) Pay $711.15 restitution to Jon Webster;
3) All other conditions remain the same as in count 1.  
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.  
Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgment.  
Minutes.
